<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 6:22PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Banks,
northeastern Jackson and northwestern Madison Counties through 700 PM
EDT...
At 622 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Banks Crossing, or near
Commerce, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Commerce, Homer, Maysville, Pinefield Crossroads and Banks Crossing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
